# Replace Employee ID With The Unique Identifier

## Problem Type
Basic LEFT JOIN

## What I Learned

- LEFT JOIN keeps all rows from the Employee table.
- Missing matching rows produce NULL values.
- Used LEFT JOIN because every employee should appear in the output.

## Pattern

Need all records from one table even if matching data doesn't exist.

Use:
LEFT JOIN

## Difficulty

Easy
##Solution

SELECT EU.UNIQUE_ID , E.NAME FROM EMPLOYEES E LEFT JOIN EMPLOYEEUNI EU ON E.ID=EU.ID;
